node.accessibility_caption: Photo by The Modern Proper in Austin, Texas. May be an image of food.

node.text:
Salmon Niçoise: Summer On A Plate!! Niçoise salad is at once filling and refreshing, and quite possibly the perfect sunny day dinner. We’ve swapped the traditional oil-packed tuna for salmon, because wild-caught salmon is a more sustainable choice and it’s also so, so pretty. Meaty, rosy-pink salmon against vibrant salad greens and bright yellow, jammy egg yolks—tucking into this salad in the sun-dappled light of a summer evening is just pure bliss.
.
.

Tap @themodernproper for link to recipe. Search “Salmon Niçoise” on the blog or HERE >>>> https://themodernproper.com/salmon-nicoise-salad

When the garden is overrun with oversized zucchini, we don’t despair or hem and haw. Rather, we get excited—it’s time to make these super cheesy, loaded zucchini boats! 
.
.
Tap @themodernproper for link to recipe. Search “zucchini skillet” on the blog or HERE >>> https://themodernproper.com/italian-stuffed-zucchini-boats
.
.

node.text:
When it’s truly too hot to even move, and certainly too hot to really cook, invite a few neighbors over (the nice ones—the ones that bring ice-cold beer and rosé) and put out a big, chilled bowl of this super easy shrimp ceviche. With plenty of chips, of course! Simple as can be, laid-back and truly fun, we’re pretty sure that dinner parties don’t get any better than that.
.
.
Tap @themodernproper for link to recipe. Search “ceviche” on the blog or HERE >>> https://themodernproper.com/shrimp-ceviche
.
.

node.text:
Juicily flavorful, and a cinch to make, we’re majorly in love with these stovetop-cooked, cilantro-lime chicken thighs. A quick marinade of lime juice and zest, chopped garlic, bright cilantro, and a touch of honey transforms boneless, skinless chicken thighs into the juicy, tender surge of sunshine that your dinner routine needs.
.
.
Tap @themodernproper for link to recipe. Search “cilantro chicken” on the blog or HERE >>> https://themodernproper.com/cilantro-lime-chicken-thighs
.

node.text:
We’ve been guilty of forgetting about sweet potatoes in the summer months. We’re all busy loading up on sweet corn and tomatoes and making potato salad by the bowlful. But, as it turns out, it’s worth remembering this ultra-healthy, kid-favorite tuber in the summer months because it gets along beautifully with the grill—smoky flavors are a natural partner for its natural sweetness—and it goes with so many main dishes that it’s a winner no matter what's for dinner.
.
.
Tap @themodernproper for link to recipe. Search “grilled sweet potatoes” on the blog or HERE >>> https://themodernproper.com/grilled-sweet-potatoes
.
.

node.text:
Why is it that zucchini is always the one veggie that literally takes over your garden all at once? If you have too much of it, like Natalie, here’s one of our favorite recipe for that beloved summer squash. This Savory, Italian-ish (hello salty-licious parmesan cheese!), Greek-ish (hello tzatziki sauce for dipping!) crispy zucchini fritter recipe that’s here to steal your thunder can be found through our link in bio. Search zucchini! 

https://themodernproper.com/mediterranean-style-zucchini-fritters-with-tzatziki-dipping-sauce
